title.rendered: Melbourne vs Brisbane, Knockout, Australian T20 League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Melbourne: Shaun Marsh, Martin Guptill, Sam Harper (wk), Aaron Finch (c), Matthew Critchley, Will Sutherland, Jonathan Wells, Tom Rogers, Corey Rocchiccioli, Kane Richardson, Fawad Ahmed

Brisbane: Usman Khawaja (c), Josh Brown, Marnus Labuschagne, Matt Renshaw, Sam Hain, Jimmy Peirson (wk), James Bazley, Michael Neser, Matthew Kuhnemann, Spencer Johnson, Mitchell Swepson

Venue: Docklands Stadium, Melbourne

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 155

2nd innings average score: 165

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good wicket for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Usman Khawaja loves batting against Melbourne. In 9 innings, he has accumulated 369 runs at 53, including 3 fifties.

Likewise, his counterpart Aaron Finch has tasted decent success against Brisbane. In 13 games, has added 505 runs at 46, including 4 half-centuries.

Shaun Marsh and Kane Richardson have enjoyed their time at Docklands. While Marsh has collected 452 runs at 42 including the highest score of 99*, Richardson has bagged 36 wickets including the best figures of 4 for 33.

When these teams met earlier in the competition, Michael Neser and Tom Rogers were the power players for bagging a four-for each.

For five consecutive games, Josh Brown has been dismissed in the single digits.

In the last 3 games at Docklands, 5 half-centuries have been smashed and all of them belong to the top-order batters.

In the same period, an average of 7 sixes per innings has been launched at the venue.
